headline: Centene (NYSE:CNC) Withdraws Full-Year Outlook Due To Enrollment Challenges
summary: Centene (NYSE:CNC) faced significant challenges last week, as its share price dropped by 37%, despite its inclusion in the Russell 1000 Defensive and Value-Defensive Indices on June 28, 2025. This index addition underscored the company's recognition for performance and stability. However, the severe price decline was largely driven by Centene's decision to withdraw its full-year outlook due to unexpected enrollment data and rising member health costs.
